<h1>Polygon area calculator</h1>

The calculator below will find the area of any polygon if you know the coor=
dinates of each vertex.
This will work for=20
<a href=3D"https://www.mathopenref.com/trianglearea.html">triangles</a>,=20
<a href=3D"https://www.mathopenref.com/polygonregular.html" title=3D"all si=
des equal and all interior angles equal ">regular</a>
and=20
<a href=3D"https://www.mathopenref.com/polygonirregular.html" title=3D"Any =
polygon that is not a regular polygon">irregular polygons</a>,=20
<a href=3D"https://www.mathopenref.com/polygonconvex.html" title=3D"A polyg=
on that has all interior angles less than 180 deg">convex</a>
or=20
<a href=3D"https://www.mathopenref.com/polygonconcave.html" title=3D"A poly=
gon that has one or more interior angles greater than 180 deg">concave poly=
gons</a>.


<p>
It uses the same method as in
<a href=3D"https://www.mathopenref.com/coordpolygonarea.html">Area of a pol=
ygon</a> but does the arithmetic for you.
</p>


